positions.title: Data Science Intern
positions.description:
Project: Intelligent Shelf Product Detection and Classification

During my internship, I worked on developing an advanced computer vision pipeline for automated shelf analysis. The project integrated multiple deep learning and feature extraction models to detect, segment, and classify products on retail shelves.

YOLOv8 was used to detect shelves and define product regions.

Detectron2 (Mask R-CNN) handled precise product segmentation.

A ResNet-50 classifier was trained to recognize and categorize products from cropped images.

ORB feature extraction with BFMatcher was integrated for additional product similarity matching and validation.

The system was tested on a large-scale retail dataset and successfully identified products across different shelves, providing annotated visual outputs with bounding boxes and class labels.

This project combined object detection, instance segmentation, image classification, and feature matching into a unified workflow, demonstrating how deep learning can automate real-world retail product recognition and inventory analysis.
